24/05/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- A former defence minister, Yiannis Varvitsiotis, leads the 24-member slate of the ruling New Democracy (ND) party for next month's European parliamentary elections. The list, presented at the weekend, also includes a former foreign minister, Antonis Samaras, as well as four current European Parliament members from ND: Antonis Trakatelis, George Dimitrakopoulos, Kostas Hatzidakis and Roda Kratsa. The party's ticket focuses on strengthening Greece's position in Europe. The main opposition party PASOK also presented its Euro-election ticket, which is headed by a member of the local business community, Mary Matsouka. (ANA - 24/05/04; MPA - 21/05/04)
